Family: tnum_correct_mul

Asserts soundness of the BPF verifier's tnum (tristate-number)
precise multiplication ('mulPrecise', alias tnum_mul): for any
concretes x in tnum (av, am) and y in (bv, bm), the value x*y lies
in the tnum returned by tnum_mulPrecise.

The algorithm is the shift-and-add construction over the bits of the
first operand, using tnum addition at each step. Quadratic in the
bit width, so the k = 32 variant has solver problems that grow
roughly with k^2 in the size of the unrolled circuit.
